#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:5
msgid "The Devpts Filesystem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:7
msgid ""
"Each mount of the devpts filesystem is now distinct such that ptys and their "
"indices allocated in one mount are independent from ptys and their indices "
"in all other mounts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:11
msgid ""
"All mounts of the devpts filesystem now create a ``/dev/pts/ptmx`` node with "
"permissions ``0000``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:14
msgid ""
"To retain backwards compatibility the a ptmx device node (aka any node "
"created with ``mknod name c 5 2``) when opened will look for an instance of "
"devpts under the name ``pts`` in the same directory as the ptmx device node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:19
msgid ""
"As an option instead of placing a ``/dev/ptmx`` device node at ``/dev/ptmx`` "
"it is possible to place a symlink to ``/dev/pts/ptmx`` at ``/dev/ptmx`` or "
"to bind mount ``/dev/ptx/ptmx`` to ``/dev/ptmx``.  If you opt for using the "
"devpts filesystem in this manner devpts should be mounted with the "
"``ptmxmode=0666``, or ``chmod 0666 /dev/pts/ptmx`` should be called."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:25
msgid "Total count of pty pairs in all instances is limited by sysctls::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:31
msgid "Per-instance limit could be set by adding mount option ``max=<count>``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:33
msgid ""
"This feature was added in kernel 3.4 together with ``sysctl kernel.pty."
"reserve``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/devpts.rst:36
msgid ""
"In kernels older than 3.4 sysctl ``kernel.pty.max`` works as per-instance "
"limit."
msgstr ""
